        <headline>Heat Advisory issued July 28 at 6:56PM EDT until July 29 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Heat index values ranging from the upper 90s to low 100s
expected Tuesday.

* WHERE...In Connecticut, Southern Litchfield County. In New York,
Eastern Albany, Eastern Greene, Eastern Schenectady, Eastern
Ulster, Northern Saratoga, Southern Saratoga, Western Columbia,
Western Dutchess, and Western Rensselaer Counties.

* WHEN...From noon to 8 PM EDT Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.

To reduce risk during outdoor work, the Occupational Safety and
Health Administration recommends scheduling frequent rest breaks in
shaded or air conditioned environments. Anyone overcome by heat
should be moved to a cool and shaded location. Heat stroke is an
emergency! Call 9 1 1.</instruction>
